<TITLE> Govt to rid Dhaka of drug abuse </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, April 7 (bdnews24.com)  Law-enforcing agencies will launch a special drive to make Dhaka city drug-free. Home minister Sahara Khatun said this at the conclusion of an inter-ministerial meeting on drug abuse on Wednesday. She said, "We will launch a special operation for a month to make the city free from drugs. The operation will start soon." The home minister hoped that drug abuse could be eliminated under the operation preventing drugs from even entering the city. She said, "A committee of police, RAB, community police and representatives from drug control and narcotics department will be formed." The home minister also said public awareness will be raised by forming different committees made up of teachers and other members of the civil society. The committees will organise awareness programmes in schools, colleges and madrassahs. b
